      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MRS MAHONEY (4) took on stronger company last time so will enjoy the drop to maiden grade having placed on debut at this level at Parkes prior. Has more upside than many of these. WINDY HILL ABBEY (5) comes through the same race and beat MRS MAHONEY home. Draws outside that rival but that was just her second start so she has scope for improvement. REDEMPTION MISS (2) has been quite consistent of late and that continued last start when she finished third at this circuit and distance. Gets the benefit of a good draw so may play a role. VINIES JOLT (3) lines up for the first time. By Village Jolt and hails from the Wendy Turnbull stable. Has been trialling well and should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. GLINDA SHANNON (8) was well fancied when resuming but manners let her down. Draws wide so can't make any mistakes but is capable of better.",
